            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>All the work of the erection of the house of the Holy Martyrs has been made for
                    the salvation and succour of Samuel and his family and for the repose of the
                    much celebrated, in the month of June, indiction 14, year 6200.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>The dating system used is not clear. Proposed dates are June 490 (using the era
                    of Diocletian), but that year fell on indiction 13. Other possibilities include
                    596 (using the Georgian era of the World) and 701 (an unknown dating system that
                    might place the incarnation at 5500).</p>
            </div>
